<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05032b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05032b">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05032b"> 32(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> catechumens &mdash; (Martin C &mdash; mass till</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">He had become a catechumen, and while he quietly followed the exercises of one, a vocation began to stir his soul. &hellip; The exercises of a catechumen consisted in attending instructions in the faith and in assisting at part of the Mass. The unbaptized were dismissed before the consecration of the Host, and on this account the portion of the service at which they were allowed to be present was called the Catechumen&apos;s Mass. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
